content.text:
You are inspecting exactly one report page image.

Decide whether this page is a repeated in-report catalogue/navigation page.

A repeated catalogue page usually:
1. shows a short list of section items in a stable order;
2. includes a heading like 目录, catalogue, or contents;
3. visually emphasizes exactly one current item to indicate the next section.

Not repeated catalogue pages:
1. a traditional front table-of-contents page that maps the full document once;
2. a section divider page with only one title;
3. a normal body page with charts, tables, or paragraphs.

If it is a repeated catalogue page, extract the ordered item list and identify the single active item.
The active item must correspond to one extracted item and should usually be returned by ordinal, such as 01, 02, 03, Part One, Chapter 2, etc.
Return JSON only.

Return this schema:
{
  "role": "catalog_repeat_page" | "not_catalog_repeat",
  "items": [
    {
      "ordinal": <string|null>,
      "title": <string>
    }
  ],
  "active_item": <string|null>,
  "confidence": "high" | "medium" | "low",
  "reason": <short string>
}

